Spring MVC application skeleton with Hibernate persistence.
Requirements:
- java 6+
- postgresql [database]
- gradle [build tool]
- junit4 [unit testing]
- WebDriver [functional testing]
- selenium [BDD cases]
- log4j [logging]


1. Edit the following files to reflect your environment:
	src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/spring/persistence-config.xml
	src/test/resources/test-persistance-config.xml

2. Start postgres server,
- create database testtrailblazers :see test-persistance-config.xml, no need to create tables inside as tests will do it
- create database trailblazers :see persistance-config.xml
        - create table item {CREATE TABLE item
                             (
                               item_id bigint NOT NULL,
                               description character varying(255) NOT NULL,
                               name character varying(255) NOT NULL,
                               price numeric(19,2) NOT NULL,
                               type character varying(255) NOT NULL,
                               CONSTRAINT item_pkey PRIMARY KEY (item_id)
                             );

                            CREATE TABLE account
                            (
                              account_id bigint NOT NULL,
                              account_name character varying(255) NOT NULL,
                              password character varying(255) NOT NULL,
                              enabled integer NOT NULL,
                              CONSTRAINT account_pkey PRIMARY KEY (account_id)
                            );

                             CREATE TABLE account_role
                             (
                               role_id bigint NOT NULL,
                               account_name character varying(255) NOT NULL,
                               role character varying(255) NOT NULL,
                               CONSTRAINT account_role_pkey PRIMARY KEY (role_id)
                             );

                             insert into account values (1,'AdminCat','admin',1);
                             insert into account values (2,'UserCat','user',1);

                             insert into account_role values (1, 'AdminCat', 'ROLE_ADMIN');
                             insert into account_role values (2, 'UserCat', 'ROLE_USER');

                             }

3. Run the unit tests:
  	gradle clean build

4. Run the Selenium tests (you will need to have Firefox installed):
	gradle clean selenium

5. Run application :
    gradle jettyRun
    [http://localhost:8080/trunk/]

Say HelloooTrailBlazers !


Intellij:
'gradle idea' sets up project files.

SVN:
http://sethholloway.com/blog/2011/03/10/svnignore-example-for-java/
`svn propset svn:ignore -F .svnignore .` [.svnignore file states the files/folders to be ignored ]
